sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth
    participant NotebookCtl as Notebook Controller
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Workbench<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>AWS Credentials
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant ModelCtl as Model Controller
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Predictor as Predictor Pod<br/>8080/TCP mTLS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>Metrics Collection

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 1: Interactive Model Development to Deployment

    User->>Dashboard: 1. Create Data Science Project<br/>Bearer Token (OAuth)
    Dashboard->>Dashboard: Create namespace with RBAC

    User->>Dashboard: 2. Launch Jupyter Workbench<br/>Select image, resources
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtl: Create Notebook CR<br/>API call via K8s API
    NotebookCtl->>Notebook: Deploy Stateful Pod<br/>+ OAuth Proxy<br/>+ OpenShift Route

    User->>Notebook: 3. Develop & Train Model<br/>HTTPS via Route<br/>OAuth Token
    Notebook->>Notebook: Train model with<br/>PyTorch/TensorFlow
    Notebook->>S3: 4. Save trained model<br/>AWS Signature v4
    S3-->>Notebook: Model artifacts stored

    User->>Dashboard: 5. Create InferenceService<br/>Model URI, Runtime
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>spec.predictor.model
    KServe->>S3: 6. Download model artifacts<br/>Storage credentials
    S3-->>KServe: Model files
    KServe->>Predictor: Deploy predictor pod<br/>Knative Service
    KServe->>ModelCtl: InferenceService event
    ModelCtl->>Gateway: 7. Create Istio Gateway<br/>VirtualService
    ModelCtl->>ModelCtl: Create OpenShift Route
    ModelCtl->>ModelCtl: Create AuthConfig (Authorino)

    User->>Gateway: 8. Inference Request<br/>POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>Bearer Token
    Gateway->>Gateway: Validate token (Authorino)<br/>SubjectAccessReview
    Gateway->>Predictor: Forward request<br/>mTLS via Service Mesh
    Predictor->>Predictor: Run inference
    Predictor-->>Gateway: Prediction result<br/>JSON response
    Gateway-->>User: HTTP 200 with predictions

    Gateway->>TrustyAI: 9. Payload logging<br/>Request/Response
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Calculate fairness metrics<br/>SPD, DIR
    TrustyAI->>Prometheus: 10. Export metrics<br/>/q/metrics endpoint
    Prometheus->>Prometheus: Scrape and store<br/>ServiceMonitor

    Dashboard->>Prometheus: 11. Query metrics<br/>Thanos Querier API
    Prometheus-->>Dashboard: Model performance data
    Dashboard-->>User: Display metrics in UI

    Note over User,Prometheus: End-to-end: Development → Training → Serving → Monitoring
